## Notes
- The input textarea is intentionally blank on page load — clicking Run without filling it returns early (highlights the field). This is correct UX, not a bug. The approval workflow requires the textarea to be filled first.
- WebGPU unavailable in headless = mock LLM responses. All UI state transitions (needs-review -> approved -> push-enabled) work identically in mock mode. Full WebGPU model path is only verifiable in Chrome with GPU hardware.
- GH Pages SPA 404 on the `/work-samples/` deep link is expected; `public/404.html` handles the redirect and React renders the correct route.

## handoff
- produced: Playwright deploy-test confirming live demo fully functional — all 28 checks pass
- decisions: 404 on `/work-samples/` route is GH-Pages SPA redirect (expected, not a bug); WebGPU tested via mock fallback (full model only available with GPU)
- next needs: media-capture — screenshot + screen recording of hero flow (fill brief -> Run Authority Engine -> output card -> Approve -> Push enabled); demo loads at `https://michaelwegter.com/demos/real-estate-intelligence-center/`
